<section id="problem" class="relative py-32 px-6">
  <div class="max-w-[800px] mx-auto">
    <!-- Section Indicator -->
    <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-10 reveal">
      <span class="font-mono text-[14px] text-forge-amber">01</span>
      <div class="flex-1 dotted-separator"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Headline -->
    <h2 class="font-serif font-normal text-primary-text leading-tight mb-12 reveal" style="font-size:clamp(32px,3.5vw,45px);letter-spacing:-0.5px;">
      The transformation industry has a dirty secret.
    </h2>

    <!-- Body -->
    <p class="font-sans font-normal text-secondary-text leading-relaxed mb-12 reveal" style="font-size:clamp(18px,1.5vw,27px);line-height:1.6;">
      Most transformation projects fail. Not because people aren't smart — because the model is broken. Consultants are paid to extend, not to finish. You get a deck, a workshop, a roadmap, and a handshake. Six months later, nothing has changed.
    </p>

    <!-- Amber Climax -->
    <p class="font-serif font-normal text-forge-amber leading-tight reveal" style="font-size:clamp(28px,3vw,36px);">
      We built Transformate because we refuse to be part of that cycle.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Momentum Line -->
  <div class="momentum-line"></div>
</section>
